dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Mendis b Chameera 26 (56b 1x4 0x6) SR: 46.42

dismissalComment.html: and gone! A slower delivery around off, the ball cuts back in, the offcutter, Mushfiqur slogs his wicket away now. Not very clever batting. Mushfiqur charges at Chameera, doesn't get to the pitch and whacks it away straight into the hands of short midwicket

dismissalText.commentary: Sabbir Rahman c sub (DSK Madushanka) b Perera 10 (12b 2x4 0x6) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: but he strikes ... Mushfiqur has something to say to Sabbir. That was an awful stroke at 57 for 4. A full delivery on middle and leg, the ball moves back in slightly, Sabbir runs down at the bowler and looks to smash him over mid-on but that inward movement takes it off the inside half and lobs to mid-on. What a chance for Sabbir, he has thrown it away.

headshotImage.caption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalComment.html: Loose, loose shot. Full and wide outside off - possibly on a sixth-stump line - Anamul simply throws his hands at the ball. He has a big swish at it and only manages to drag a thick inside edge back onto the stumps. The leg stump is tilted back. Anamul has a long stare at the bowler, he can't believe what he has done. He has bagged a six-ball duck. The search for a solid opening partner for Tamim continues

Another stunning piece of fielding from Danushka. His brilliance in the field has sent back both Shakib and Tamim. He throws himself to his right from backward point now, stretches out with both hands, and snaffles a catch. Credit to Lakmal too for banging it short just a shade outside off, surprising the batsman and forcing him to splice a catch. It actually reared up from a back of a length

Lakmal has bounced out Mahmudullah! There was only one man at the boundary on the leg side and the batsman has picked out Chameera at fine leg. This was a plan: dig it short and attack the body with assistance from leg-gully and fine leg. This chest-hunting ball rushes Mahmudullah into the hook and he holes out. Excellent bowling and excellent fielding to boot from Sri Lanka

wow, how do you get out to that? A short delivery drifts down leg, Nasir looks to swivel into a pull and hit it for six, but all he can do is get a bit of bat on that. Flies to Dickwella's left, and he takes it. Would have been wide, but he wanted a boundary. 80 for 8 now

dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan run out (Gunathilaka) 8 (8b 2x4 0x6) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Danushka, you beauty! He throws the stumps down from backward point at the striker's end but catch Shakib short. Huuuuuge wicket for Sri Lanka. This was even shorter and outside off, punched into the cover-point region. Danushka tears across to his left, swoops down on the ball and nails the stumps.Tamim called for the single, there was a brief hesitation between the wickets, and Shakib gave up in the end. Danushka is one of the best fielders in the SL side. Can't take him on

dismissalText.commentary: Abul Hasan c †Dickwella b Perera 7 (7b 1x4 0x6) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: 128 kph and taken! So Sri Lanka continue to strike, but Abul Hasan reviews after speaking to Mushfiqur. He should have known. It's a full delivery outside off, the ball comes back in, takes the inside edge and carries through to Dickwella, who dives away to his right. That's an appalling review, you only get one in ODIs, and Mushfiqur or any other batsman can't review now if they get a shocker. A big spike on UltraEdge.

commentTextItems.html: short and aimed at the body, shovelled away to the square-leg region, and SL secure a 10-wicket win. They have wrapped up the match in 35.5 overs

commentPostTextItems.html: 3.11pm "After a long time, we played out A game," says Dickwella." We just stuck to our plan and executed it well."

There it is. Sri Lanka set up a final with the hosts. After having conceded 320 just six days ago, Sri Lanka, led by Lakmal, skittled Bangladesh for 82. They did not even need the services of Akila Dananjaya. Danushka and Tharanga then had some fun in the chase to close out the match.

Mashrafe: Tamim and Shakib have been scoring runs. Mushy did well but hopefully the others will come up with good knocks. They are working hard, so we can't complain. Hopefully, the boys will deliver in the final. All the batters said it was a good wicket to bat on. Maybe the application wasn't there. It was a bad day and hopefully it does not count in the final.
Chandimal: Before the game, we had gameplans, credit goes to the players. We got the energy in the bowling - especially Suranga. Upul and Danushka finished it off well. Credit to them also.
Lakmal is the Man of the Match
That's a wrap of this match. Done in just 35.5 overs. Until next time, goodbye.
Lakpj: "this 50 game and the NZ-Pak T20 match started at the same time. while the t20 game is still under way this game is done and dusted. "
Anver Azeez: "A strong comeback by SL !! wish this will boost their confident before the Final !!"

commentTextItems.html: short on middle, cramps Danushka for room, beats the pull, and hits him on the body
back of a length and outside off, Tharanga employs the latest of late cuts and sends the ball to deep third man
dug in on middle, ducks under it
back of a length and nips in on off from around the wicket, cramps Tharanga for room, blocked back to the bowler
Danushka attempts a wild reverse-swat and watches the ball slide past the leg stump

commentTextItems.html: Danushka gets inside the line of this length ball and works it to square leg
tossed on middle, Tharanga stays leg-side of the ball and belts it away to the right of mid-off
floated up outside off, he leans into it, caressing the ball through the covers. What a smooth shot
dropped short and wide outside off, Tharanga rocks back and cracks it past backward point, where the fielder throws himself to his right to stop the ball
fired outside leg, slips past the bat, slips past the keeper and into the boundary
slid through on off stump, played back to the bowler

commentPostTextItems.html: Sandeep: "@Showkat Khan. As a Sri Lankan fan who lived through 2017, i'd gladly take this one game"

commentTextItems.html: clipped off the pads to square leg for another single

commentPreTextItems.html: Showkat Khan: "@Udara - Any team can have a good day or even a bad one. Judgement should be based upon over a period of games rather than just one game. "

commentTextItems.html: tip and run to backward point. SL closing in on the final spot

commentPostTextItems.html: anver azeez: "T20 like start by SL !! raining sixes here..."

commentTextItems.html: back of a length and skids in on middle, nurdled to midwicket off the back foot

commentPreTextItems.html: Madusha olupath: "Hopefully this will be the turning point for Sri Lanka cricket.."

commentTextItems.html: another bouncer over the shoulder, zings through to the keeper for another wide

commentPostTextItems.html: Kamsy: "Tharanga really is making a point here, once Kusal Perera his back there will be a huge competition for opening slots. Tharanga is showing here he can be aggressive too. Brilliant stroke making! "

commentTextItems.html: just short of a good length and outside off, muscled across the line to the right of deep midwicket

commentPreTextItems.html: Ramitha: "When was the last time you saw Tharanga hit 3 sixes and no fours!"

commentTextItems.html: bouncer outside leg, ducks under it, wide

commentPostTextItems.html: Pasan: "Remember the name... Sri Lanka it is... You never know when they hit you right in your face. Australia had a bit of it. Pakistan had bit of it. South Africa had a bit of it. India had bit of it .Now Bangladesh is having the same in their own back yard"

commentTextItems.html: hip-high short ball on the off stump, Danushka lines it up and swats it powerfully over square leg. Bam!
deflected off the hips to short fine leg

the slog sweep is taken at long-on! A googly outside off, Rubel clears his front leg and slogs the ball into the hands of long-on. Bangladesh are bowled out for 82, their ninth-lowest ODI total

headshotImage.longCaption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: Anamul Haque b Lakmal 0 (6b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Loose, loose shot. Full and wide outside off - possibly on a sixth-stump line - Anamul simply throws his hands at the ball. He has a big swish at it and only manages to drag a thick inside edge back onto the stumps. The leg stump is tilted back. Anamul has a long stare at the bowler, he can't believe what he has done. He has bagged a six-ball duck. The search for a solid opening partner for Tamim continues

headshotImage.caption: Danushka Gunathilaka player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Danushka Gunathilaka player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan run out (Gunathilaka) 8 (8b 2x4 0x6) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Danushka, you beauty! He throws the stumps down from backward point at the striker's end but catch Shakib short. Huuuuuge wicket for Sri Lanka. This was even shorter and outside off, punched into the cover-point region. Danushka tears across to his left, swoops down on the ball and nails the stumps.Tamim called for the single, there was a brief hesitation between the wickets, and Shakib gave up in the end. Danushka is one of the best fielders in the SL side. Can't take him on

headshotImage.caption: Danushka Gunathilaka player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Danushka Gunathilaka player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tamim Iqbal c Gunathilaka b Lakmal 5 (14b 0x4 0x6) SR: 35.71

dismissalComment.html: Another stunning piece of fielding from Danushka. His brilliance in the field has sent back both Shakib and Tamim. He throws himself to his right from backward point now, stretches out with both hands, and snaffles a catch. Credit to Lakmal too for banging it short just a shade outside off, surprising the batsman and forcing him to splice a catch. It actually reared up from a back of a length

headshotImage.caption: Dushmantha Chameera player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dushmantha Chameera player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah c Chameera b Lakmal 7 (20b 1x4 0x6) SR: 35

dismissalComment.html: Lakmal has bounced out Mahmudullah! There was only one man at the boundary on the leg side and the batsman has picked out Chameera at fine leg. This was a plan: dig it short and attack the body with assistance from leg-gully and fine leg. This chest-hunting ball rushes Mahmudullah into the hook and he holes out. Excellent bowling and excellent fielding to boot from Sri Lanka

dismissalText.commentary: Sabbir Rahman c sub (DSK Madushanka) b Perera 10 (12b 2x4 0x6) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: but he strikes ... Mushfiqur has something to say to Sabbir. That was an awful stroke at 57 for 4. A full delivery on middle and leg, the ball moves back in slightly, Sabbir runs down at the bowler and looks to smash him over mid-on but that inward movement takes it off the inside half and lobs to mid-on. What a chance for Sabbir, he has thrown it away.

headshotImage.caption: Niroshan Dickwella player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Niroshan Dickwella player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Abul Hasan c †Dickwella b Perera 7 (7b 1x4 0x6) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: 128 kph and taken! So Sri Lanka continue to strike, but Abul Hasan reviews after speaking to Mushfiqur. He should have known. It's a full delivery outside off, the ball comes back in, takes the inside edge and carries through to Dickwella, who dives away to his right. That's an appalling review, you only get one in ODIs, and Mushfiqur or any other batsman can't review now if they get a shocker. A big spike on UltraEdge.

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Mendis b Chameera 26 (56b 1x4 0x6) SR: 46.42

dismissalComment.html: and gone! A slower delivery around off, the ball cuts back in, the offcutter, Mushfiqur slogs his wicket away now. Not very clever batting. Mushfiqur charges at Chameera, doesn't get to the pitch and whacks it away straight into the hands of short midwicket

dismissalText.commentary: Nasir Hossain c †Dickwella b Chameera 3 (13b 0x4 0x6) SR: 23.07
